File: Health Minister Zweli Mkhize. AFP/Rodger Bosch JOHANNESBURG -  Health Minister Zweli Mkhize says the number of new COVID-19 cases in the Eastern Cape is concerning. According to the Minister, the number of new COVID19 infections is currently higher than the numbers seen in July and August. He also adds that infections are rising in other provinces. READ: COVID-19: SA reports 88 new deaths South Africa's latest statistics reflect 3,069 new COVID-19 cases as well as 88 deaths. The total number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in South Africa stands at 778, 571. SA's COVID-19 death toll has surpassed 21,000.